  <refsection>
    <title>GUI</title>

    <para>The <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel> dialog box allows you to specify
    properties of a <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel> such as as maximum iterations,
    cost function tolerance, feasibility tolerance, choice of reporting
    options, and choice of whether or not to use the central difference
    derivative method.</para>

    <para>To create a <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel> resource, navigate to the
    <guilabel>Resources</guilabel> tree, expand the
    <guilabel>Solvers</guilabel> folder, highlight and then right-click on the
    <guilabel>Optimizers</guilabel> sub-folder, point to <guilabel>Add
    </guilabel>and then select <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel>. This will create a
    new <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel> resource, Yukon1. Double-click on Yukon1 to
    bring up the <guilabel>Yukon</guilabel> dialog box shown below.</para>

